  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p><span style=\"font-family:Roboto, sans-serif\">The Bastion represents the desire to protect, and the understanding that all forms of Defense can be used as a great offense. </span>The Bastion's Shield exemplifies this need to protect others, and the lengths one will go to help them.</p><p><span style=\"font-family:Roboto, sans-serif\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;scrollbar-width:initial;scrollbar-color:initial\">Constellation: </strong>@UUID[Compendium.immortal-ardor.deities.Item.3PJqDBXSNoaagwY8]{The Bastion}</span></p><hr /><p><strong>First Asterism</strong> (Level 1): You gain the @UUID[Compendium.immortal-ardor.spells.Item.X7pev2hUW8PSSwVw]{Bastion's Shield} innate spell. You also gain a +1 status bonus to Fortitude saving throws.</p><p><strong>Second Asterism </strong>(Level 9): You can cast this spell or any other Second Asterism Nebula Facet spell an additional time in a day. The bonus increases to +2.</p><p><strong>Third Asterism </strong>(Level 17): You can cast this spell or any other Third Asterism Nebula Facet spell an additional time in a day. The bonus increases to +3.</p>"
